snippet: The Gold Cup, which is usually dominated by the United States and Mexico, has had several surprising results in the group stages of this year’s tournament.
abstract: Group stages of the Concacaf Gold Cup, usually dominated by United States and Mexico, have seen several surprising results in 2015 tournament; Trinidad has emerged atop Mexico in its group, just one of several factors that have made for fascinating quarterfinal round.
lead_paragraph: The Gold Cup, which is usually dominated by the United States and Mexico, has had several surprising results in the group stages of this year’s tournament.
